(763, 88, 'description', 'A terrestrial creature that is also mythical, Makara seeks to address our common narratives that have disappeared through time and to re-familiarise them through art. This mural of ZERO’s interweaves multiple forms of beloved stories in varying contexts. The work affirms the notion of art’s versatility in giving different narratives, perspectives and meaning for a vibrant community such as Little India.\r\n\r\n<em>Photo copyright @ 2018 Steve Golden.</em>'),
