(785, 92, 'artist_bio', 'A’shua Imran is a multidisciplinary Singaporean artist who predominantly works with painting, performance, photography and installation. He founded Mural Lingo in 2014, an independent platform that focusses on creating opportunities for artists to practice mural painting and engage with their community. He has exhibited locally and internationally, and recently completed an artist residency at Bag Factory Artists’ Studios in Johannesburg, South Africa.'),
