(819, 98, 'artist_bio', 'Izzad’s practice is deeply intertwined with his belief in collaboration and the study of relationships between people and the everyday. Having graduated from LASALLE College of The Arts with a BA (Hons) Fine Arts in 2013, he had his first solo exhibition at the Institute of Contemporary Arts Singapore in 2017 and has participated in numerous exhibitions in Singapore and Indonesia. He was recently an artist-in-residence at The Substation, Singapore.'),
