(868, 107, 'artist_bio', 'Tinu’s practice is a critical study into the political and poetic symbols of the female form – an awakening from her previous 15-year-long modeling career. An MA Fine Arts graduate from LASALLE College of The Arts, she was the recipient of the President’s Award at the International Biennial of Contemporary Art (Italy) in 2015 and the Winston Oh Travel Research Award in 2016.'),
