(1676, 313, 'artist_name', 'Shah Rizzal'),
(1677, 313, '_artist_name', 'field_5a4c9c7a6faa3'),
(1678, 313, 'artist_bio', 'Shah Rizzal, a graffiti artist and muralist with an untameable spirit, has a poetic stance on space and art, which has constantly spurred his imagination and conception on how to bridge the gap between art and the audience. Drawing inspiration from the streets, Shah’s art hopes to communicate to others his experiences in relation to his surroundings, as comments or critics of the present state/space.'),
