(2010, 358, '_artist_name', 'field_5a4c9c7a6faa3'),
(2011, 358, 'artist_bio', 'Nadiah Alsagoff (b. 1991) is an interdisciplinary artist based in Singapore. She has graduated with a BA(Hons) Fine Art degree from LASALLE College of the Arts – Goldsmiths University of London. She is interested in the relationship between the body, the self and its position in the everyday world and with other beings. Having grown up in a culturally mixed background, namely Arab, Chinese and Sarawakian, she often finds herself in a space between cultures.\r\n\r\nHer work stems from her position in a culturally mixed setting and looks at themes of identity and existence, how people are born into a world of predetermined circumstance, and how identities are contextualised beings, tied to the world by their bodies.\r\n\r\nFormally trained as a painter, she also explores these themes through the use of the body in video and performance.'),
