(2049, 367, 'description', 'What did men and women trade along these old spaces and worn paths? There are whispers of what might have been along these alleys and buildings. Indian mythology is rife with tales of rebirth, gender fluidity and karma. <em>Flowers of the Night</em> invites listeners to a sensory storytelling experience by Kamini Ramachandran.  Surrender to the fragrance that lingers in memories.\r\n\r\nFeaturing poetry by Shivram Gopinath.'),
