(2101, 374, 'description', 'SIFAS is proud to present an exciting performance combining both Bharatanatyam and Kuchipudi to illustrate on the differences and similarities of both classical dance forms. The performance will showcase each dance form individually and then together in a duo performance, with songs which reflect on the theme of fragrance in the poetry of the lyrics and variety of ragas.\r\n\r\nThis Bharatanatyam-Kuchipudi duo <em>jugalbandi</em> presentation by teachers P K Geethanadhan and Amrita Lahiri seeks to educate on the diversity of the classical Indian dance forms and hearkens back to the vibrant past of dance and other performing arts which took place in Little India’s streetscape in the early 20<sup>th</sup> century.'),
