(2131, 379, 'description', 'The Coffin is Too Big for the Hole is one of Singapore’s best-known monologue written by Kuo Pao Kun. This is a fresh retelling of Kuo Pao Kun’s popular satirical monologue with a blend of traditional and contemporary elements, conveyed by a young Indian woman in modern day society.'),
