(93, 1, '2017-12-14 12:07:50', '2017-12-14 04:07:50', '', 'The Voyage of the Arya-Dravidians', 'Paying tribute to the rich Indian culture in Little India as well as other cultures that harmoniously share this space, A’shua Imran envisioned our ancestors’ voyage to Singapore. Using a selection of objects, prints, sketches, poetries and photographic images as inspiration to narrate a fabled crew of Indian sailors, each segment in the mural reveals different encounters of the wanderers – reflecting the thoughts, plans and material collections that points to their histories and identities.', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '3-ashua-imran_the-voyage-of-the-arya-dravidians_2018', '', '', '2017-12-14 12:08:07', '2017-12-14 04:08:07', '', 92, 'http://artwalklittleindia.sg/adm/wp-content/uploads/3.-Ashua-Imran_The-Voyage-of-the-Arya-Dravidians_2018.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(94, 1, '2017-12-14 12:08:15', '2017-12-14 04:08:15', '', 'A’shua Imran', 'A’shua Imran is a multidisciplinary Singaporean artist who predominantly works with painting, performance, photography and installation. He founded Mural Lingo in 2014, an independent platform that focusses on creating opportunities for artists to practice mural painting and engage with their community. He has exhibited locally and internationally, and recently completed an artist residency at Bag Factory Artists’ Studios in Johannesburg, South Africa.', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ashua-imran', '', '', '2017-12-14 12:08:22', '2017-12-14 04:08:22', '', 92, 'http://artwalklittleindia.sg/adm/wp-content/uploads/A’shua-Imran.jpeg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
