(387, 2, '2018-12-15 12:46:25', '2018-12-15 04:46:25', 'LASALLE College of the Arts and Singapore Tourism Board (STB), with thesupport of the Little India Shopkeepers’ and Heritage Association (LISHA),\npresent ARTWALK Little India, a multi-disciplinary public art project set in the\ncultural precinct of Little India.\n\nThe inaugural edition of ARTWALK was held in 2015 and the event has been\npart of the Singapore Art Week line-up ever since. In 2018, the event featured\n9 artworks and brought in close to 270,000 visitors over a 10-day event period.\n\nThrough artworks such as wall murals, films, music and performances, artists\nbring to life the history and traditions of Little India, as well as the personal\nstories of its community through a multi-sensory art experience.', 'About the Event', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '10-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-12-15 12:46:25', '2018-12-15 04:46:25', '', 10, 'http://artwalklittleindia.sg/adm/2018/12/15/10-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
