(1106, 126, 'description', 'Explore the basics of putting pencil and pen to paper with Craft Varies, a Singapore-based practice established for self-discovery through the connection of mind and body. \r\n\r\n<strong>About the Instructor: </strong>\r\nCraft Varies was founded by Clarence Valerius Wee (b. 1988), who discovered his passion for typography during the course of his tertiary education in graphic design. In order to better understand the anatomy of alphabetical forms, he went back to basics and dedicated himself to mastering calligraphy – he has been practicing for over eight years now. In 2013, he travelled to San Francisco to pick up sign-painting craft and techniques from established sign-painters, New Bohemia Signs.\r\n\r\nFor more information, please visit <a href=\"http://www.tamarthouse.com/product/wellness-in-writing-workshop/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">tamarthouse.com</a>'),
